1 (5) Emergency medical communications shall be provided in
2 accordance with rules adopted by the commission.
3 (6) A nontransporting emergency medical services vehicle must
4 conform with the commission's requirements.
5 SECTION 2. IC 36-8-10.5-7, AS AMENDED BY P.L.93-2024,
6 SECTION 209, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS
7 [EFFECTIVE JANUARY 1, 2026 (RETROACTIVE)]: Sec. 7. (a) The
8 education board shall adopt rules under IC 4-22-2 establishing
9 minimum basic training requirements for full-time firefighters and
10 volunteer firefighters, subject to subsection (b) and section 7.5 of this
11 chapter. The requirements must include training in the following areas:
12 (1) Orientation.
13 (2) Personal safety.
14 (3) Forcible entry.
15 (4) Ventilation.
16 (5) Apparatus.
17 (6) Ladders.
18 (7) Self-contained breathing apparatus.
19 (8) Hose loads.
20 (9) Streams.
21 (10) Basic recognition of special hazards.
22 (b) A person who fulfills the certification requirements for:
23 (1) Firefighter I; or
24 (2) Firefighter II;
25 is considered to comply with the requirements established under
26 subsection (a).
27 (c) In addition to the requirements of subsections (a), (d), and (f),
28 the minimum basic training requirements for full-time firefighters and
29 volunteer firefighters must include successful completion of a basic or
30 inservice course of education and training on sudden infant death
31 syndrome that is certified by the Indiana emergency medical services
32 commission (created under IC 16-31-2-1) in conjunction with the state
33 health commissioner.
34 (d) In addition to the requirements of subsections (a), (c), and (f),
35 the minimum basic training requirements for full-time and volunteer
36 firefighters must include successful completion of an instruction course
37 on vehicle emergency response driving safety. The education board
38 shall adopt rules under IC 4-22-2 to operate this course.
39 (e) In addition to the requirements of subsections (a), (c), (d), and
40 (f), the minimum basic training requirements for full-time and
41 volunteer firefighters must include successful completion of a basic or
42 inservice course of education and training in interacting with
