10 firefighters and to manage the stress and trauma related to
11 employment as a firefighter;
12 (2) recognition of:
13 (A) symptoms of posttraumatic stress disorder; and
14 (B) signs of suicidal behavior; and
15 (3) information on mental health resources available for
16 firefighters.
17 (g) In addition to the requirements of subsections (a), (c), (d),
18 (e), and (f), the minimum basic training requirements for full-time
19 and volunteer firefighters must include successful completion of a
20 basic or inservice course of education and training in interacting
21 with individuals with Alzheimer's disease and dementia that is
22 certified by the Indiana emergency medical services commission
23 created by IC 16-31-2-1.
